18. Modes of Operation

18.1 Review Mode

Analyzes existing content and produces:

* inferred audience,
* developmental fit,
* risks,
* likely interpretations,
* linguistic frames,
* recommended edits.

18.2 Generation Mode

Creates content for a specified audience profile.

18.3 Adaptation Mode

Transforms one artifact into variants for different audiences.

Example:

One concept
  ├── age 4 version
  ├── age 7 version
  ├── age 10 version
  ├── teen version
  └── adult version

18.4 Moderation Mode

Flags or routes content based on audience suitability.

18.5 Curriculum Mode

Sequences content across developmental stages.

18.6 Parent or Teacher Mode

Explains why content may be suitable or unsuitable.

18.7 Creator Coach Mode

Teaches creators how to better model their audiences.

