29. Anti-Patterns

29.1 Adult nostalgia disguised as children’s content

Content is aesthetically childlike but linguistically and socially adult.

29.2 Engagement-first developmental design

The artifact is optimized for attention capture rather than healthy experience.

29.3 Safe-topic fallacy

A benign topic is assumed harmless despite manipulative framing.

29.4 Forbidden-topic fallacy

A sensitive topic is assumed harmful regardless of treatment.

29.5 Age-number reduction

Age is used as the only developmental variable.

29.6 Cultural universalism

One family’s preferences are treated as universal truth.

29.7 Validation without calibration

The system affirms internal interpretation without checking external facts.

29.8 Calibration without empathy

The system provides facts while ignoring likely emotional impact.

29.9 Overprotection

All ambiguity, challenge, fear, or sadness is removed.

29.10 Synthetic sameness

AI-generated content converges toward one tone, one morality, and one model of humanity.

