34. Ethical Data Collection

Children are not simply a source of training data.

Data collection must include:

* informed parental consent,
* age-appropriate assent,
* privacy protection,
* minimal data retention,
* no covert emotional experimentation,
* no manipulation for engagement,
* independent oversight,
* and clear research purpose.

Canonical principle:

Do not exploit children to build a system intended to protect children.

⸻

