37. Canonical Operators

Lens

View content from the audience’s developmental position.

Infer

Infer the audience implied by the artifact.

Translate

Preserve truth while changing developmental resolution.

Temper

Reduce emotional, sensory, or cognitive overload.

Contextualize

Add information required for correct interpretation.

Scaffold

Provide intermediate steps between current capacity and intended understanding.

Reframe

Change the cognitive coordinate system through which the content is interpreted.

Simulate

Estimate likely audience interpretation and imitation.

Trace

Follow linguistic and cultural effects downstream.

Compare

Evaluate multiple age adaptations against the same invariant.

Escalate

Route uncertain or high-impact cases to human review.

