39. Canonical Maxims

The audience is not a demographic label. It is a model of a mind.

Content does not merely enter attention. It participates in development.

Age appropriateness is not topic avoidance. It is resolution, framing, timing, and context.

Every linguistic frame privileges certain forms of thought.

The strongest guardrail is a person who understands why the boundary exists.

Engagement is not evidence of developmental benefit.

Simplify the representation, not the truth.

A safe system protects the child without flattening the world.

AI should not teach humans to resemble the average machine-model of humanity.

We must tell the machine what kind of humans we are trying to become.

